        "body":  "Codex review: NEEDS_CORRECTION\n\nFinding: `crates/editor-egui-host/src/menu_tests.rs:9` still contains the exact split-exemption marker string inside the new module doc comment:\n\n```rust\n//! ?1.3 Rule 3 1000-line split cap and retires its `// SPLIT-EXEMPTION:`\n```\n\nThis PR correctly removes the active annotation from `lib.rs`, and `lib.rs` is now 915L. But the architecture lint treats `// SPLIT-EXEMPTION:` as a substring anywhere in a `.rs` file (`txt.contains(EXEMPTION_MARKER)`), so if `menu_tests.rs` ever grew past 1000L this historical note would accidentally satisfy the lint as an exemption. It also means a crate-wide grep still reports a split-exemption marker in `editor-egui-host`, even though the purpose of the PR is to retire that debt.\n\nPlease reword the header to avoid the exact marker string, e.g. ?retires the prior line-cap annotation? / ?retires the split-exemption annotation? without the literal `// SPLIT-EXEMPTION:` token. The extracted test body itself is behavior-identical: I compared the old inline body against the new sibling file body after dedent and they match.\n\nCI note: architecture lints/fmt are green; workspace tests and CodeQL Rust are still in progress at the time of review.\r\n",
